I"0<p>Most people believe there is an absolute $10,000 yearly limit for buying electronic Series I Savings Bonds. You can buy some more using your personal tax return, but there’s a little known way to legally buy even more!</p>

<h1 id="using-trusts">Using Trusts</h1>

<p>Remember, In the United States, trusts are technically their own legal entity. As such, a trust named “John Smith” would be distinct from an individual named “John Smith”. That’s pretty strange!</p>

<p>So how does this help us? Well, if one had enough free time and money to set up 5 trusts with themselves as the trustee as follows:</p>

<ul>
  <li>John Smith Trust 1</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 2</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 3</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 4</li>
  <li>John Smith Trust 5</li>
</ul>

<p>They’d now be able to buy upto $50,000 in Series I Savings Bond using 5 separate TreasuryDirect entity accounts.</p>

<p>Of course, this requires enough patience and willpower to use the TreasuryDirect website. (Buying and selling hopefully coming soon to TreasuryViewer 🤠)</p>

